Knogo Corp. said it settled patent litigation with Allied-Signal Corp. at a cost of $600,000. 

The suit involved the use of certain alloys in Knogo's electronic article surveillance systems.
The company makes anti-shoplifting systems for retailers. 

Knogo said the settlement cost will be reflected in the second quarter ended Aug. 31.
In the year-ago period, the company had net income of $1.5 million, or 29 cents a share, on revenue of $14.8 million. 

